      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): respect explicit PI runtime policy",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRespect explicit PI/OpenClaw runtime policy when Codex is intentionally unavailable.\n\nThis keeps the existing OpenAI/Codex default behavior unchanged, but makes explicit PI config authoritative in three places:\n\n- config validation no longer emits a missing `@openclaw/codex` install warning when OpenAI routes are explicitly pinned to PI/OpenClaw or `plugins.entries.codex.enabled` is explicitly `false`\n- doctor stale-plugin diagnostics suppress only intentional `plugins.entries.codex` missing-plugin noise while still reporting legitimate stale policy refs (`plugins.allow` / `plugins.deny`) and explicitly enabled missing Codex entries\n- doctor session route repair preserves explicit PI/OpenClaw session runtime pins while rewriting stale `openai-codex/*` route metadata to canonical `openai/*`\n\nThe missing-Codex suppression intentionally does **not** apply when `plugins.entries.codex.enabled === true`, even if OpenAI is pinned to PI/OpenClaw; that remains a real missing-plugin warning.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `npm exec -- pnpm test -- --run src/config/config.plugin-validation.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/stale-plugin-config.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/codex-route-warnings.test.ts`\n  - config plugin validation: 43 passed\n  - stale-plugin config: 15 passed\n  - Codex route warnings: 105 passed\n- `npm exec -- pnpm check:test-types`\n- `npm exec -- pnpm lint:core`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nCommands were run from this branch after rebuilding source checkout dist via `pnpm dev`. Paths below use isolated temp homes; no real user config was modified.\n\n### Explicit PI/OpenClaw policy + missing Codex entry: quiet\n\nConfig excerpt:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"models\": {\n    \"providers\": {\n      \"openai\": {\n        \"baseUrl\": \"https://api.openai.com/v1\",\n        \"models\": [],\n        \"agentRuntime\": { \"id\": \"pi\" }\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"plugins\": { \"entries\": { \"codex\": {} } },\n  \"agents\": { \"list\": [{ \"id\": \"openclaw\" }] }\n}\n```\n\nCommand:\n\n```sh\nOPENCLAW_DISABLE_BUNDLED_PLUGINS=1 \\\nOPENCLAW_HOME=/tmp/oc-proof-pr88723-disabled-bundled/home \\\nHOME=/tmp/oc-proof-pr88723-disabled-bundled/home \\\nnpm exec -- pnpm -- dev doctor\n```\n\nCodex/stale diagnostic grep:\n\n```text\n--- codex/stale/plugin installed lines ---\n│  - model-usage: bins: codexbar                                           │\n│    install option: Install CodexBar (brew cask)                          │\n```\n\nNo `plugins.entries.codex`, `plugin not installed: codex`, or stale `codex` plugin diagnostic is emitted for the intentional PI/OpenClaw setup.\n\n### Explicitly enabled missing Codex plugin: still warns\n\nConfig is the same except:\n\n```json\n\"plugins\": { \"entries\": { \"codex\": { \"enabled\": true } } }\n```\n\nCommand:\n\n```sh\nOPENCLAW_DISABLE_BUNDLED_PLUGINS=1 \\\nOPENCLAW_HOME=/tmp/oc-proof-pr88723-enabled-bundled/home \\\nHOME=/tmp/oc-proof-pr88723-enabled-bundled/home \\\nnpm exec -- pnpm -- dev doctor\n```\n\nRelevant doctor output:\n\n```text\n◇  Config warnings ────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\n│  - plugins.entries.codex: plugin not installed: codex — install the  │\n│    official external plugin with: openclaw plugins install           │\n│    @openclaw/codex                                                   │\n\n◇  Doctor warnings ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮\n│  - plugins.entries.codex: stale plugin reference \"codex\" was found.     │\n│  - Run \"openclaw doctor --fix\" to remove stale plugin ids and dangling  │\n│    channel references.                                                  │\n```\n\nRefs #88706.\n",
